text=:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a:Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a:Title: Double negatives in AAVE%0a:Author: ahana_m%0a:Section: D%0a:Completed: 24.04.2021 - 08:12%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210505-020348-368450#%0a* [-04.05.2021 - 19:03-] || TA_lili marked as complete%0a#foxend 210505-020348-368450#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aas title says%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aI looked at a reddit post titled “old lady steals seat at graduation and refuses to move.” It had a video embedded in it of an old African American lady at a graduation who is trying to sit in a seat. Someone asks her to move and she says “you don’t save no seat for nobody.”%0a%0aThe person who posted says “I hate when IDIOTS use a double negative, do they know how stupid they sound.”%0a%0aThis is clearly an example of discrimination against speakers of AAVE. It’s an argument that stigmatizes the use of the double negative since this person clearly doesn’t understand that even though it not be a prevalent construction in Standard American English, it is prevalent in AAVE. A double negative is also known as negative concord where more than one negative is used within a sentence but you still interpret the sentence as having one negation. %0a%0aNegative concord is also used in Polish, Hebrew, and Italian. People don’t look at it as “illogical” or “idiotic” in these other languages, so it doesn’t make sense to call it illogical in AAVE.%0a%0ahttps://slate.com/human-interest/2018/07/linguistic-prejudice-in-sorry-to-bother-you-is-a-real-world-problem.html%0a%0ahttps://www.reddit.com/r/badlinguistics/comments/e3wldl/people_who_use_double_negatives_are_idiots/%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_lili:)
